  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As of node ~v14.0.0~ v16.9.0 the `Error` type supports error chaining by passing an [optional second argument of type `{ cause: any }` to the constructor of `Error`](https://tc39.es/ecma262/multipage/fundamental-objects.html#sec-error-message), with the value of that `cause` property appearing as the value of the [`cause` property on the resulting `Error` instance](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Error/cause).\r\n\r\nWe should update the constructor of `@truffle/error` to implement the same pattern, and where possible, pass the underlying cause to the super constructor.\r\n\r\nOptionally we should also consider [polyfilling](https://github.com/zloirock/core-js#ecmascript-error) the Error class to support error chaining for versions of Node prior to ~v14.0.0~ v16.9.0.",
